@startuml bb84-intrusion
!theme plain
title BB84 Eavesdropper Detection & Key Redistribution

participant "Alice\n(Sender)" as A #LightGreen
participant "Eve\n(Eavesdropper)" as E #LightCoral
participant "Bob\n(Receiver)" as B #LightBlue
participant "QBERMonitor" as M #LightYellow
participant "Video Stream" as V #LightGray

== Normal Operation (No Eavesdropper) ==

A -> B : Quantum key exchange\n(QBER ≈ 2-4%)
M -> M : Record QBER: NORMAL
V -> V : Video encrypted with\ncurrent key (AES-128)

note over A, B, V #LightGreen : Key rotates every 3 seconds\nVideo continues uninterrupted

== Eve Begins Intercept-Resend Attack ==

A -[#red]> E : Alice sends photon\n(encoded in basis +)
E -> E : Measure in random basis\n(50% chance of wrong basis)
E -[#red]> B : Re-send photon\n(may be in wrong state)

note over E #LightCoral : When Eve's basis ≠ Alice's basis:\nBob gets random bit → ~25% error

== QBER Rises ==

B -> M : Report QBER: 0.08
M -> M : Classify: **WARNING**
M -> V : Emit warning event\n(yellow indicator)

B -> M : Report QBER: 0.15
M -> M : Classify: **WARNING**

B -> M : Report QBER: 0.24
M -[#red]> M : Classify: **INTRUSION DETECTED**\nQBER (24%) > threshold (11%)

== Key Rejection ==

M -[#red]> V : Emit intrusion_detected event
note over V #LightYellow : Dashboard shows red alert\nQBER chart spikes

M -> A : **ABORT** current key round
M -> B : **ABORT** current key round

note over A, B #LightCoral : Key material discarded\nOld key remains in use

== Automatic Re-Keying ==

A -> B : Retry key exchange\n(0.5s retry interval)

alt Eve Still Present
    A -[#red]> E : Photon intercepted again
    E -[#red]> B : Re-sent
    B -> M : QBER still > 11%
    M -> M : **ABORT** again
    note over M : Consecutive failures logged\nIntrusion count incremented
else Eve Removed / Stops
    A -> B : Clean quantum channel
    B -> M : QBER: 0.03
    M -> M : Classify: NORMAL
    M -> V : Emit key_redistributed
    note over V #LightGreen : Dashboard returns to green\nNew key applied to video stream
end

== Video Stream Continuity ==

note over V #LightGreen
  Throughout the intrusion event:
  • Video stream never stops
  • Old key continues encrypting
  • New key applied seamlessly
  • User sees QBER alert in dashboard
end note

@enduml
